{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 By default, when a tree opens none of the nodes are expanded. The\par
user can double click on a node, or press the \lquote +\rquote  button, to expand the tree as needed.\par
\par
However, you can selectively expand the tree when it opens. This is done using the \cf2 Auto expand\cf1  control\par
property. If Auto Expand is Yes, or has an Expression that evaluates to True, then the node expands.\par
\par
In this example you can specify one node to expand, and the tree will open with that node expanded. Or, if you specify zero, all nodes will expand.\par
}
